        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (undercounter)</td><td>$1,400 to $2,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (modular)</td><td>$1,800 to $2,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator replacement (scale-damaged)</td><td>$1,500 to $3,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$900 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="price-note">Cleaning compliance is the single biggest cost driver on cube ice machines. A neglected machine that destroys its evaporator at year 5 to 7 costs $1,500 to $3,000 to repair vs $200 to $340 per cleaning visit twice a year.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Nine reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Three-architecture expertise.</strong> Manitowoc vertical evaporator, Scotsman horizontal spray, Hoshizaki cell-and-curtain. Different machines, different failure patterns. We know which is which by serial number.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certification.</strong> Required for post-2020 cube machines on hydrocarbon refrigerant. See our <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 Universal (#1346255700410) page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Cleaning service that prevents 60% of "no ice" emergency calls.</strong> Twice-yearly cleaning is the cheapest insurance on a $4,000 to $12,000 cube machine.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board diagnostic codes</strong> read correctly first time. F2, E1, EF on Manitowoc; system fault codes on Hoshizaki KM-Edge; Prodigy ELITE smart board codes on Scotsman.</li>
      <li><strong>Water filter management.</strong> 3M Cuno, Pentair Everpure, OptiPure, Manitowoc K-Series.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering, no emergency surcharge.</strong> $120 anytime.</li>
      <li><strong>Common cube machine parts on the van.</strong> Water inlet valves, harvest sensors, fan motors, bin sensors.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus BBB A+.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, Orange County, Ventura.</strong> Next-day for Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister cluster: <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/">commercial refrigeration repair</a>. Soft-serve sibling: <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/soft-serve/">soft-serve machine repair</a>. Parent niche: <a href="/commercial/">commercial appliance repair overview</a>.</p>
